n  \in \mathbb N
p(x) = \left(x + \frac 1x\right)^{n}
 \begin{align} \sum_{k=0}^n {n \choose k} x^{n-k} \left(\frac 1x\right)^{k} &= \sum_{k=0}^n {n \choose k} x^{n-2k}\\ &={n \choose 0}x^{n}+{n \choose 1}x^{n-2}+\dots+?\text{ (what's the last term in the sum?)} \end{align} 
 p(x) = a_ox^{b_o}+a_1x^{b_1}+...+a_nx^{b_n} = {n \choose 0}x^{n}+{n \choose 1}x^{n-2}+\dots+? 
x^{n-k}\left(\frac 1 x\right)^k
